david giovacchini moves to penn sulair sulair home searchworks e journals databases off campus access ask us sulair news logo sulair news home all articles submit article search sulair news library web sites searchworks databases az socrates google books google scholar search this site sulair news about sulair news back issues get email announcements submit article user login login with your sunet id home groups sulair news david giovacchini moves to penn david giovacchini will be leaving stanford for the university of pennsylvania to head up their middle east collection in the van pelt library after 7 years of bringing his expertise to stanford not only in cataloging but also in music cinema and middle east studies in general david was more than ready to move on to head up a major collection at an ivy league library during his tenure at stanford david managed to build our world renowned collection of middle eastern music film and cinema memorabilia he curated an exhibit of egyptian film posters at the reception opening the exhibit the renowned and lovely egyptian film actress yusra and her director in the hit film the yacoubian building attended up until the day of his departure he will be assisting in mini exhibit of turkish film posters in the library that will also travel to washington dc for the annual meeting of the middle east studies association to accompany several panels on modern turkish cinema we all will miss david's expertise on the stanford campus all are invited to attend a farewell coffee in the mcdermott suite on monday september 19 at 2 00 david's last day at stanford will be september 29 please drop by and wish david well in his new position submitted by jeilts stanford edu on mon 09 12 2011 14 42 back stanford university stanford california 94305 650 725 1064 terms of use copyright complaints
